<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>On September 18, 2018, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="On September 18, 2018, I spoke at the Hannah Community Center for LSJ Storytellers. The theme was &quot;Are We There Yet?&quot;. In this story, I spoke about my wife and our challenges having children, dealing infertility, and working with foster children and adoption as well as dealing unexpected challenges. (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.lansingstatejournal.com/story/news/local/2018/09/30/what-you-should-know-lansing-storytellers-project-2019/1334235002/" target="_blank">I spoke at the Hannah Community Center for LSJ Storytellers,</a> a bi-monthly event where professionally coached, local storytellers of all ages share their best stories. The theme for September was "Are We There Yet?". In this story, I spoke about my wife and our challenges having children, dealing infertility, and working with foster children and adoption as well as dealing with unexpected challenges. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

